arrayElementRef is an object reference, so you need VM access to prevent GC.
appendixElementRefFromInvokeDynamicSideTable and appendixElementRefFromInvokeHandleSideTable are similar, they all read element from an array, and the logic is simple, I don't think they has to be in a function. Can you do something like the following?
void* invokeCacheLocation = owningMethod->methodTypeTableEntryAddress(callSiteIndex);
TR::VMAccessCriticalSection getReferenceElement(fej9);
uintptr_t arrayElementRef = fej9->getReferenceElement(*invokeCacheLocation, 1);
